    <field name="scopecontent_teim">The Brooklyn Sunday Review provides Brooklyn-wide news coverage of art, music, drama, clubs and organizations, politics, religion, and literature. Birth announcements, wedding announcements, and obituaries do not appear in the paper. Notices of daily church services appear regularly as does a column entitled "Weekly Review" which highlights the week's events in Brooklyn. A section called "Ladies Department" covers women's fashion and shopping news. A "Masonic" column provides news of Masonic meetings, rites, and ceremonies in and around the borough. Poems, short sketches, and stories are regularly published. Advertisements appear throughout.</field>
